    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1862-07-02T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1862-07-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="347"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d347">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Pruyn</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                        Seward</persName>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 35.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States in Japan</hi>, <hi
                                rend="italic">Yedo</hi>,</placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1862-07-02">
                            <hi rend="italic">July</hi> 2, 1862.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> The Japanese government now send to this
                    legation, four times each week, eight of their officers to be instructed in
                    speaking the English language, pursuant to the arrangement stated in my despatch
                    No. 25. In this number are included the two interpreters, next in rank to
                    Morzama, the interpreter in chief, now with the embassy in Europe.</p>
                <p>I cannot but regard this familiar intercourse with officials, through whom all
                    foreign intercourse is and will be conducted, as highly calculated to insure a
                    continuance of the good feeling now happily existing.</p>
                <p>I have the honor to be, sir, very respectfully, your most obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>ROBERT H. PRUYN, <hi rend="italic">Minister Resident in Japan.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>Hon. <hi rend="smallcaps">William H. Seward</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Secretary
                            of State, Washington.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
